Text: ship 6709 - fire - on taxi out with both engines running, left engine stator eicas message and received indication that the left engine shutdown. tower notified flight crew that they saw a visible fire from left engine, one fire bottle was discharged. corrective action : maintenance confirmed no evidence of a fire, suspect tail pipe fire. confirmed electronic engine controllers fault s, replaced left engine permanent magnet alternator stator, electronic engine controllers, vsv actuator ( adjusted ) and fire bottles. complied with operational checks and leak checks per amm, no faults noted.

Text: suspected fuel leak, left engine. shutdown not required per qrh. 700 left b difference in 30 min. fuel flows : left engine 3.6 ; right engine 3.7. performed engine run of lt engine and inspected for leaks iaw amm 71-00-00. found no evidence of leaks from engine or fuel tanks. aircraft found to be serviceable per service letter 767-sl-28-035-a.
Label: No

Text: captain reported the nr 2 engine fuel filter bypass light illuminated at engine start. aircraft grounded. performed fim 73-05, task 801. inspected and found the nr 2 engine fuel differential pressure switch connector loose. secured the connector. performed electronic engine controllers test, no faults found iaw amm 73-21-00. performed idle leak check, no leaks noted iaw amm 71-00-00. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : return to block part name : connector part condition : loose
Label: No

Text: aircraft in base maintenance : cracked cabin floor support break assembly panel at bs 540 and left butt line 2. replaced break assembly panel per srm 51-40-02.
Label: No

Text: air turn back - emergency declared - lt engine fire indication on eicas and fuel control switch. acticated on climb and then extinguished after about 45 seconds resulting in an air turn back - flight landed wout incident. replaced, torqued and safetyed said tee duct ref left engine. ref cf6 engine manual 72-00-00 engine pipi ng assembly ran engine all indications and leak ck normal secured.

Text: air temperature cont cab in " forward " position indicates 100 + at cruise. flight attendant reports hot air in cabin rows 6-10. gauge fluctuates at times when in forward and cont cab position. grounded - yes. initial evaluation showed all gauge readings normal. suspect intermittent fault. cleaned flight deck and cabin sensor filters. performed fim task 21-61 task 858 and 21-61 task 859. system operated normally. temperature in cabin and flight deck reflected what was on gauge. nature of condition : other precautionary procedure : other part name : filter part condition : contaminated

Text: aircraft was grounded : 1 hour and 30 minutes into flight right fuel tank indicated 2600 less than left tank. center tank was supplying, totalizer normal and fuel burn symetric. aircraft was left wing heavy, suspect weak right center pump. maintenance replaced center tank right hand refuel valve iaw amm 28-21-02, replaced center tank right hand defuel valve iaw amm 28-26-01, replaced center tank right hand #6 fqis tank unit amm 28-41-02 and performed satisfactory operational check.
